The paper deals with statistical learning, optimization, and regularization, which are all topics that fall under the umbrella of machine learning. The use of Wasserstein distances and distributional robustness suggests a focus on generative models and adversarial training, which are common in the field of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses statistical models and discrete choice models, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.ML (Machine Learning).
